707946f-a.text:
Second Avenue, east side, north from E. 96th to 97th Streets, showing the westerly portion of the Second Avenue Railroad car barn as viewed northeastward under the Second
Avenue "E1".
Note the bus which has replaced the street cars that formerly emanated daily from this structure.
S-otewder 14, 1938.
P.L. Sperr

714874f-a.text:
E. 96th Street, west from Second Avenue, showing buildings on the south side of this thoroughfare. Note the upgrade that reaches its peak at Park Avenue. Overhead is the Second Avenue "El". Former tenements at the N.W. corner of Second Avenue and 96th Street have been demolished and a sign erected there. The photographer is standing in front of the car barn and viewing southwestward.
September 14, 1938.
P.L. Sperr

714875f-a.text:
E. 96th Shreet, east from Second Avenue, showing on the north side of this street one side of the old car barn of the Second Avenue Railroad Co. On the opposite side and near First Avenue is P.S. No. 150. Note the power plant and stack of the New York Railways Co. on the East River. View No. 2 shows only the car barn and the Second Avenue "E1".
August 1933.
View 2:September 14, 1938.
Geo. . Balgue
P.L. Sperr
Same as view 2, from a different angles looking westward
from First Avenue.
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS  April 25, 1941
